# Fix Audit Log Filter

## Goal
Resolve the "Error loading data" issue on the Audit Log page when filtering by action.

## Root Cause
The [AuditLog.tsx](file:///c:/SCOUTNEW/scout_db/frontend/src/pages/Audit/AuditLog.tsx) component sends uppercase values ("CREATED", "UPDATED", "REVERTED") for the `action` query parameter. Use of uppercase values causes a validation error in the backend because the [AuditAction](file:///c:/SCOUTNEW/scout_db/src/scout_db/models/override.py#26-32) enum expects lowercase values ("created", "updated", "reverted").

## Proposed Changes

### Frontend
#### [MODIFY] [AuditLog.tsx](file:///c:/SCOUTNEW/scout_db/frontend/src/pages/Audit/AuditLog.tsx)
- Update [AuditEntry](file:///c:/SCOUTNEW/scout_db/frontend/src/pages/Audit/AuditLog.tsx#20-30) type definition to use lowercase action values.
- Update [Select](file:///c:/SCOUTNEW/scout_db/frontend/src/components/shared/DataTable.tsx#52-63) items to use lowercase values (`value="created"`, etc.).
- Update `Badge` logic to check for `action === "reverted"`.
- Add a helper to capitalize the action label for display in the Badge.

